=========================================================
        StringBuffer vs StringBuilder in Java
=========================================================

Feature                 : StringBuffer
---------------------------------------------------------
Introduced In           : Java 1.0
Thread Safety           : Thread-safe
Performance             : Slower due to synchronization
Synchronization         : Methods are synchronized
Memory Efficiency       : Slightly less efficient
Execution Speed         : Lower execution speed
Suitable For            : Multi-threaded environments
Data Safety             : Provides data consistency between threads
Usage                   : Used when security and synchronization are required
Preferred In            : Banking, server-side applications
Method Behavior         : Safe for shared objects
Modification Operations : append(), insert(), delete(), reverse()
Object Creation         : Changes existing object without creating a new one
Efficiency in Loops     : Less efficient in loops
Common Methods          : append(), insert(), delete(), reverse()

=========================================================

Feature                 : StringBuilder
---------------------------------------------------------
Introduced In           : Java 1.5
Thread Safety           : Not thread-safe
Performance             : Faster because no synchronization
Synchronization         : Methods are not synchronized
Memory Efficiency       : More memory efficient
Execution Speed         : Higher execution speed
Suitable For            : Single-threaded environments
Data Safety             : No protection for concurrent access
Usage                   : Used when high performance is required
Preferred In            : Competitive coding, desktop applications
Method Behavior         : Best for local objects
Modification Operations : append(), insert(), delete(), reverse()
Object Creation         : Changes existing object without creating a new one
Efficiency in Loops     : More efficient in loops
Common Methods          : append(), insert(), delete(), reverse()

